    \noindent\textbf{3.8} A company has signed a delivery contract with a customer for equipment. The quarterly production capacity, production cost per unit, and delivery quantity at the end of each quarter are shown in Table 3-30. If equipment produced in one quarter is not delivered during that quarter, a storage and maintenance fee of 0.1 thousand yuan per unit per quarter is incurred. Question: Under the condition of meeting the delivery contract, how should the company arrange its production schedule throughout the year to minimize the total annual cost(in thousand yuan)? 

\begin{table}[h]
    \centering
    \caption{Table 3-30: Quarterly Production Capacity, Delivery Quantity, and Production Cost}
    \label{tab:production}
    \begin{tabular}{cccc}
        \toprule
        Quarter & Production Capacity (units) & Delivery Quantity (units) & Production Cost per Unit (thousand yuan) \\
        \midrule
        1 & 25 & 15 & 12.0 \\
        2 & 35 & 20 & 11.0 \\
        3 & 30 & 25 & 11.5 \\
        4 & 20 & 20 & 12.5 \\
        \bottomrule
    \end{tabular}
\end{table}
